<section class="hero">
  <h1>Your <em>Bitcoin Deployment Plan</em></h1>
  <div class="hero-subtitle">You have money to put into Bitcoin. Deploy it all now, spread it out, or do some of each?</div>
  <p class="subtitle">Model your own plan &mdash; your sum, your cadence, your horizon &mdash; see how it would have fared across real history, and how it might fare ahead.</p>
</section>

<main class="content-area">

  {% include 'components/tool-framing.njk' %}

  <div class="section-intro dp-prose">
    <p>This is the companion to <a href="/lump-sum-or-ladder-in">Lump Sum or Ladder In?</a> &mdash; where that page shows the general lesson, this one is about your situation. Set a sum to deploy, pick a style, and compare deploying it all at once, laddering it in, or a <strong>hybrid</strong> of the two.</p>
    <p class="dp-footnote"><strong>DCA</strong> &mdash; dollar-cost averaging: deploying a fixed amount on a regular cadence (e.g. every paycheck) as a savings discipline, rather than all at once.</p>
  </div>

