  <!-- ════════ PREREQUISITE + METHODOLOGY + ATTRIBUTION ════════ -->
  <section class="dp-section">
    <div class="belief-context">
      <div class="belief-context-label">A note on prerequisite reading</div>
      <p><strong>This tool uses the Power Law channel to frame the decision.</strong> If that model isn&rsquo;t useful to you, neither is this page. <a href="/the-power-law#channel">The Channel</a> lays out the bands, the evidence, and the attribution &mdash; read it first if the frame is new.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="dp-attribution">
    <span class="dp-attribution-label">Channel framework &amp; coefficients</span>
    The Power Law channel &mdash; floor at 0.42&times; trend, upper band at 3&times; trend &mdash; was developed by <a href="https://www.porkopolis.io/thechart/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>Matthew Me&zcaron;inskis</strong></a> at Porkopolis Economics. Coefficients used: <code>a = 1.6&times;10<sup>&minus;17</sup></code>, <code>b = 5.77</code>. See <a href="/the-power-law#channel">The Channel</a> for the full case and attribution.
  </div>

  <div class="dp-method">
    <div class="dp-method-label">Methodology</div>
    <ul>
      <li>Channel position is the log-space location between floor and ceiling: <code>(ln(price/trend) &minus; ln 0.42) / (ln 3.0 &minus; ln 0.42)</code> &mdash; 0 at the floor, 1 at the upper band.</li>
      <li><strong>Retrospective &mdash; channel-anchored (default):</strong> finds every historical entry whose channel position is within &plusmn;0.07 of today&rsquo;s live position, deploys your plan from each at real prices, and holds for the chosen horizon &mdash; reported as a <em>distribution</em> (median + typical range across the matches), with the chart replaying the most recent match. The horizon slider sets <em>how long you hold</em>, not which entry. <strong>Time-anchored (secondary):</strong> deploys the horizon&rsquo;s-worth of years ago from today and replays to now &mdash; a single historical path.</li>
      <li><strong>Projective</strong> deploys today and extends two Power Law paths &mdash; reversion-to-trend and stay-on-trajectory &mdash; as a range. Both are extrapolations of an empirical regularity, <em>not forecasts</em>.</li>
      <li>Lump deploys the full sum at once; ladder spreads it equally over the chosen duration; hybrid deploys a chosen share now and ladders the rest. Value is BTC accumulated &times; price along the path; multiples are amount-invariant, the dollar figures just scale with the sum.</li>
      <li>Commitment backstop: mean value-multiple by hold length, <strong>8-year exit convention</strong> (nearest sample to entry&nbsp;+&nbsp;8&nbsp;&times;&nbsp;365.25&nbsp;days); ~1&ndash;3% sensitivity. Worst-entry recovery is the range for entries above 1.5&times; channel position, recovered to the latest sample.</li>
      <li id="dpMethodWindow">Computed live from the current <code>PL_DATA</code> window.</li>
      <li>Today&rsquo;s channel position is computed at load from the latest sample and the live spot (CoinGecko, via the shared fetch) &mdash; never baked in.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

